The paper discusses neuromorphic engineering, which is a subfield of computer science that focuses on designing hardware and software systems inspired by the brain. The paper specifically discusses large-scale neuromorphic spiking emulators, which are used to simulate neural models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Other likely sub-categories include cs.ET (Embedded Systems), cs.AR (Hardware Architecture), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
